What topics are covered in CONVenient Workshop?
CONVenient covers: Neural Networks, Convolution Operation, CNNs, Building Alphabet Classifier, Model Deployment.

What are the prerequisites for CONVenient Workshop?
Prerequisites: First/second order differentiation intuition, Kaggle account, Flask installed.

What are the prerequisites for Fusion 3C0 Generative Design Workshop Workshop?
Prerequisites: Laptop with Fusion 360 installed, Stable internet.

Q: How long is the hackathon?
A: The hackathon lasts for 10 hours, from 8:00 AM to 6:00 PM. The day will include coding time, mini-games, and a final presentation session.

Q: How many people can be on a team?
A: Teams can consist of 2 to 5 participants. Teams must be formed before the event and registered with the AURORA website.

Q: What are the mini-games, and how do they affect my score?
A: Mini-games will be announced at the event. They will take only 15 minutes total. Winning can slightly boost your score, but preference will always be given to your app.

Q: Do we need to bring our own laptops?
A: Yes, each team must bring their own laptops and devices. The venue will provide internet access.

Q: How do I register for the hackathon?
A: Registration will commence on the AURORA website.

Q: What are the judging criteria?
A: Innovation and originality, Practicality and scalability, Real-world problem solving, Implementation difficulty, and Quality of final pitch presentation.

Q: What behaviors result in disqualification?
A: Any form of cheating, plagiarism, or unsportsmanlike behavior will result in disqualification.

Q: What are the prizes?
A: 1st Place: ₹8,000, 2nd Place: ₹4,000, 3rd Place: ₹3,000. All participants receive certificates.

Q: Who is Arpan Garg?
A: Arpan is Co-founder & CTO of Exa Protocol, a two-time SIH winner, ex-Product Head of Coding Ninjas, and built Commudle (Google for Startups Accelerator program).

Q: What topics will be covered in the Tech Talk?
A: Finding, validating, and transforming ideas into products, Essential skills for meaningful projects, and a collaborative brainstorming activity with live feedback.
